My hands are small and chubby.....I’m also envious of ppl who have anime fingers, skinny and long. 🥹 I can’t wear any rings coz that makes my fingers look like sausage in the hotpot 😭 

My fingers are also very dry. Sometimes they’re so dry and my skin cracked and started to bleed... 🩸It’s no fun when it’s caught by yarn, you don’t want to feel that , ouch! 😰

Now I’ve learned to put the lotion on before bed since I can’t work with yarn when my hands are full of lotion

Why am I selling on Ribblr @ribblr_it ? 
Because it’s awesome! 🤩

As a smol biz owner, I’m very happy to find a platform like Ribblr that offers LOW to FREE FEES to sellers! 🥹You can earn points with your link to lower your sale fees (with $elFee points) to zero fees. This is a big relief for me since Etsy charges much higher fees. 

You can also edit to the pattern when you find a typo or you’d like to update the pattern without creating a new listing,  it’ll automatically edit the pattern for everyone who owns it from your ribblr shop. 

Of course, you can also sell finished makes and the original designer earns royalties! 😉

Last but not least, you can also convert your Ribblr Pattern into a PDF if you like to print the pattern off for you to read. 👍🏻

Ribblr not only benefits the crochet pattern designers, it also benefits all the crochet /knit lovers! They have flash sales, freebies, and giveaways all the time! The community is very supportive there as well, so as the customer service! 🤌🏻

Did I mention that I met so many creative and awesome crochet artists through Ribblr as well? 😍

Thank you for making my small business grow in 2022, Ribblr! I’m looking forward to grow with you and Ribblr in 2023!

✨This is my favorite sewing tool before I sew the parts together for making my crochet dolls. 
I use the T-pins to place the parts into the doll and see how it looks before the last assembly steps.

These T pins help to secure the parts steady, you can also sew along while the pins are still on. I use this a lot to make sure the parts will be at the right spot that I want them to be!

I also tried it for my bigger plushies, mostly blanket yarn, too and I’d just have to use more of these T pins coz the yarn is thicker. The T-shaped head helps to pin the connecting parts better as well.

👉You can find these T-pins in the “my favorite tool “ section in the link in my bio! I hope this info helps!

✦ Updated ✦  Hello! everyone! My recent pugbee pattern has been getting some negative attention. I made this pattern based on a 2017 pugbee . Another designer reached out to me and accused me of stealing the design she made in 2021. I hadn’t seen her pugbee before she messaged me, but tried to talk with her to come up with a solution.

I made a Bee My Loaf last year, this year I simply changed Bee My Loaf into this pug with heart wings and in pink valentines theme. I don’t think there’s a problem to publish the old pattern design i haven’t published yet.

Unfortunately, she has since started a campaign against me and continues to claim I stole her design / pattern even though I made my pugbee design back in 2017.

Here's the update on Feb 1st, 2023 from the platform that investigated this case : 

" We take claims of this status very seriously and investigate thoroughly before making a decision, and as we checked both instructions we found that they were not the same. of course, as you know, no one can take ownership of any animal, but their design featured a combination of elements, and that's why we asked you to make changes" -by @ribblr_it

Designers will often have similar inspirations, but it doesn’t mean that we are stealing each other’s designs. We should celebrate each other and not bring each other down.

I never thought I’d have to explain why/how/when I design my art. I've turned off comments and not interacted with all the cyberbullying from the trolls, simply because it does not solve this issue but creates more chaos. I'm glad it's now all cleared up. 

All the bullies who spread false accusations and harassed me and other designers will be ignored and blocked. 

Thank you for reading my side of the story. I hope this is clear enough.
Sorry for my other designer friends who are being harassed by these trolls and bullies..

Thank you for all your DMs for support. 

Carrie

😅I’ve been told that my doll price is too expensive and I’m sure I’m not the only one who hears this all the time😉

🫨 how do you price your handmade crochet item?
I price my item based on my design, the effort I put into it, how much time I need to make it plus my skills, the details, the size, and the material. 

Sometimes I have customers asking for a big discount coz they ordered 2 different dolls. But making 2 different dolls requires double or more time /materials/details to make, it’s really hard to give a big discount, especially for handmade crochet items. 

Sometimes I have customers wondering why the “smaller” doll costs more or the same as the big plushie? this goes to the details. Sometimes smaller is not cheaper and some small detailed dolls actually require more effort to make. 

Sometimes I have customers telling me that their grandmother can make this for them FOR FREE , i feel bad for their grandmother coz they don’t appreciate her obviously. 

I don’t feel bad when ppl ask these types of questions, I’m always happy to answer them and most of them are very understanding and still purchase from me. 🥰

other than that, everything was great! Thank you for stopping by and supporting my smol business!! 🥰
